	"content": "<h1 class=\"page-title\">Week 2</h1>\n  \n  <div id=\"todo-date-mount-point\"></div>\n  \n    <p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Overview</span></strong></p>\n<p>Capital preservation (economic paradigm, optimal asset allocation problem), supply of financial assets (real vs financial assets, assets supplied by governments, zero-net supply assets, ultra short-term assets), investment process (asset classes, consumers' investment holdings, investment approaches) and financial markets (money and capital markets)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Learning Objectives</span></strong></p>\n<p>Upon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the economic paradigm associated with the investment allocation problem</li>\n<li>where financial assets come from</li>\n<li>the building blocks of investment process</li>\n<li>the main asset classes</li>\n<li>the money market and the capital markets</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Preparation for class</span></strong></p>\n<p>Mandatory reading:</p>\n<p>Lecture 1: <span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"lecture 1.pdf\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/80252013?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/80252013\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">lecture 1.pdf</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/80252013/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.9