	"contentText": "Week 2\n  \n  \n  \n    Overview\nCapital preservation (economic paradigm, optimal asset allocation problem), supply of financial assets (real vs financial assets, assets supplied by governments, zero-net supply assets, ultra short-term assets), investment process (asset classes, consumers' investment holdings, investment approaches) and financial markets (money and capital markets)\n \nLearning Objectives\nUpon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:\n\nthe economic paradigm associated with the investment allocation problem\nwhere financial assets come from\nthe building blocks of investment process\nthe main asset classes\nthe money market and the capital markets\n\n \nPreparation for class\nMandatory reading:\nLecture 1: lecture 1.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 1.pdf\nSupplements: lecture 1 sup.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 1 sup.pdf\nWRDS Materials: investments-the-sp500-slide-deck.pptx\n    \n\nDownload investments-the-sp500-slide-deck.pptx\n \nClass\nClass zoom link: Class logistics\n \nAssignments and Quizzes\nA1\n \nAdditional Resources\nChapters 1 and 2\nFlow of Funds in the US: https://www.federalreserve.gov/releases/efa/enhanced-financial-accounts.htm\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nFutures markets: https://www.cmegroup.com/\n    \n\nLinks to an external site. and https://www.ice.com/about/exchanges-clearing\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nOptions markets: https://www.cboe.com/\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\n \nClass Notes\nAug 26 class recording:\nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/lWVRIkAMWP_0MNX2V_9yhTxzTo8_YqbDpL5qQCClnhuFHGziDFZLkWwDoPJZ0wyN.oH9lLqh89LkfA9Oj\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: h7QBs%#5\n \n \nAug 28 class recording:\n\nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/Tl78gG3QZRZ2Udv-ZmC9eBLf8zWSHPaviinkaltVdbG52bXZZWcwlOjpLDhZQJHE.bH9_KBxRJHWR1Jd0\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: 1d1a*^1R\nClass notes: Fnce 3030 Aug 28.pdf\n    \n\nDownload Fnce 3030 Aug 28.pdf\n\n  \n  \n